      How to=C2=A0meme
   =20
 =20
Nothing here is ever=C2=A0investing=C2=A0advice, but I do sometimes give ou=
t free=C2=A0corporate finance=C2=A0advice.[1] The big theme of that advice =
recently has been that, if you are a public company that is in a position t=
o attract meme-driven retail investors, you might as well lean into meme st=
uff.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CSay words about crypto,=E2=80=9D  I recently advised cor=
porate chief executive officers.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CSay words about electric car=
s. Tweet a picture of a dog. Your stock will go up.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CThis =
is how finance works now,=E2=80=9D I wrote, a different time;=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9Cthe goal is to say as many meme-trade buzzwords as possible because that=
 is what makes stocks go up.=E2=80=9D When your stock goes up, you will be =
able to raise money to spend on  doing good business things. This is perhap=
s the place to mention that I was once an equity capital markets banker at =
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. I=E2=80=99d be saying it there too. I think. I don=
=E2=80=99t know.=C2=A0Anyway, where was I, oh, right, GameStop is doing NFT=
s now:GameStop Corp. is launching a division to develop a marketplace for n=
onfungible tokens and establish cryptocurrency partnerships, according to p=
eople familiar with its plans, pushing the company into much-hyped areas as=
 it tries to turn around its core videogame business.The retailer has hired=
 more than 20 people to run the unit, which is building an online hub for b=
uying, selling and trading NFTs of virtual videogame goods such as avatar o=
utfits and weapons, according to the people. The company is asking select g=
ame developers and publishers to list NFTs on its marketplace when it launc=
hes later this year, the people said.GameStop also is close to signing part=
nerships with two crypto companies to share technology and co-invest in the=
 development of games that use blockchain and NFT technology, as well as ot=
her NFT-related projects, the people said. The retailer expects to enter in=
to similar agreements with a dozen or more crypto companies and invest tens=
 of millions of dollars in them this year, the people said.And=C2=A0Bloombe=
rg News reports:It=E2=80=99s also discussing with partners the potential fo=
r creating a number of funds, of up to $100 million each, to invest in NFT =
content creators and gaming companies. Over the last few months, GameStop h=
as assembled a team of more than 20 people that are focused on the crypto-r=
elated push, the person said.=C2=A0The Wall Street Journal earlier reported=
 on GameStop=E2=80=99s crypto and NFT plans. The shares jumped 29% in exten=
ded trading.Of course! For one thing,=C2=A0GameStop Corp. is=C2=A0perhaps t=
he memeiest of the meme stocks,[2] so why shouldn=E2=80=99t it meme this me=
me. For another thing, NFTs  basically=C2=A0are=C2=A0a video-game asset cla=
ss; AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0another very meme-y meme=
 stock =E2=80=94=C2=A0has been  flogging NFTs for a month or so=C2=A0with n=
o particular product logic, but =E2=80=9Cwe sell computer games and also st=
uff that you can=C2=A0own in computer games=E2=80=9D makes a lot more sense=
.=C2=A0Also though they=E2=80=99ve been saying this for months? We  talked =
last May about how GameStop had an NFT website and was hiring for its NFT t=
eam. My Bloomberg Opinion colleague Tae Kim (who also wrote about GameStop=
=E2=80=99s NFT push in May) tweeted yesterday that this is old news, and th=
at =E2=80=9Cthis re-hash leak probably doesn't bode well for their holiday =
sales report.=E2=80=9D I mean! That=E2=80=99s the corporate finance advice =
I would give!Client: We are getting preliminary numbers from our=C2=A0holid=
ay sales season and it doesn=E2=80=99t look great.Me, a corporate finance a=
dviser: Sorry to hear that.Client: What would your corporate finance advice=
 be about how to get out in front of this news?Me: Definitely say some stuf=
f about NFTs.Client: You said that last May.Me: Did you do it?Client: Yes.M=
e: Did the stock go up?Client: Yes.Me: So do it again.Client: But at this p=
oint it=E2=80=99s old news, it=E2=80=99s not like we have any substantive n=
ew developments to announce, last May we said we were planning to do NFTs a=
nd the stock went up but we=E2=80=99re still in the planning stages and =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0Me: Shh, shh. Say you=E2=80=99re planning to do=C2=A0NFTs. Peop=
le love that and have extremely short memories.I cannot stress enough how e=
asy corporate finance is now.=C2=A0=C2=A0I will say, I do not personally th=
ink that the future of the world economy will be a metaverse in which most =
of the value is created by people selling each other the right to use image=
s=C2=A0in video games. But I cannot=C2=A0rule out=C2=A0that possibility, an=
d smart people seem to take some form of it seriously. And if that=C2=A0is=
=C2=A0the future, why shouldn=E2=80=99t GameStop be a leader in the busines=
s of creating and monetizing online community and status? That=E2=80=99s  w=
hat the GameStop saga=C2=A0is:=C2=A0People came together in an online commu=
nity (to talk about GameStop), and they seized on a token of that community=
 (GameStop stock) as a speculative asset and made it go up a lot. NFTs, sam=
e basic idea. In a sense GameStop really is the expert=C2=A0here.
